reviews.review_text: good audience quality. I had 7/1/73 aud for years and now I check this one out,and I was impressed.Songs are well played and the sound is smooth.

I hate noise reduction. It sounds like someone used noise reduction on this - the high end is missing. I could be wrong - it may be just the recording or the age of the tape. It's too bad cause it's a great show. Heck, I don't think they played any bad shows in '73. I'd love to hear this aud without the NR. Three stars for sound quality. 5 stars for performance.

Muddy The recording is muddy but listenable. Certainly not up to the recording standard of the following night.

That said, this is a really energetic and fun show that roars from the very first note of The Promised Land.
